            <title>[PIG-2242] Allow the delimiter to be specified when calling TOKENIZE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2242</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The TOKENIZE function is a wrapper around the Java StringTokenizer class.  The delimiter argument is currently hard coded as &quot; \&quot;,()*&quot;, and it is impossible to specify an alternative delimiter.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The delimiter can be added as an optional argument to TOKENIZE which will preserve backwards compatibility while allowing users to specify their own delimiter chars.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
